This paper deals with the impact of hardware impairments on cell-free massive MIMO systems, which are wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also discusses the network architecture and deployment of cell-free systems, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also presents a novel hardware-quality scaling law, which is related to control systems and falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with the efficiency of the system, which is related to multimedia systems and falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the practical impact of hardware impairments, which is related to computer networks and falls under cs.COM (Computer Networks and Communications).
